# File: specs/feature-add-first-class-epic-support-and-multi-pr-delivery-flow-to-nmg-sdlc/feature.gherkin
#
# Generated from: specs/feature-add-first-class-epic-support-and-multi-pr-delivery-flow-to-nmg-sdlc/requirements.md
# Issues: #149

Feature: First-Class Epic Support and Multi-PR Delivery Flow
  As an nmg-sdlc plugin maintainer (interactive) and as the SDLC runner (automated)
  I want the SDLC to natively handle features that span multiple PRs
  So that I never have to improvise coordination structures on top of the pipeline

  # --- /draft-issue: Epic classification and body format ---

  Scenario: Epic option is offered when multi-phase signals fire
    Given a draft-issue prompt with a description referencing "in phases" and four or more distinct components
    When /draft-issue reaches Step 2 classification
    Then "Epic" is offered as a third option alongside Feature and Bug
    And the Epic option is labeled as Recommended
    And the one-line description reads "A coordinated set of child issues delivering one logical feature across multiple PRs"

  Scenario: Epic body uses the coordination template
    Given the user selects Epic in Step 2 classification
    When Step 6 synthesizes the issue body
    Then the body contains a Goal section
    And a Delivery Phases table with columns Phase, Child Issue, Depends On, Summary
    And a Success Criteria section delegating ACs to child issues
    And a Child Issues checklist
    And it contains no User Story, no Acceptance Criteria, no Functional Requirements

  Scenario: Unattended mode never auto-selects Epic without explicit signal
    Given .claude/unattended-mode exists
    And the description contains multi-phase signals but no "Type: epic" line
    When /draft-issue reaches Step 2 classification
    Then the classifier defaults to Feature and does not invoke AskUserQuestion

  Scenario: Epic label is lazily created and applied
    Given an Epic issue is being created
    And the "epic" GitHub label does not yet exist
    When /draft-issue Step 10 runs
    Then the "epic" label is created via gh label create
    And the epic issue is created with labels "epic" and "enhancement"
    And each child issue is created with label "enhancement" but not "epic"

  Scenario: Child issues are linked to their epic
    Given an Epic issue #E is created
    When /draft-issue Step 10 creates the child issues from the Delivery Phases table
    Then each child issue body contains "Depends on: #E"
    And each child is set as a GitHub sub-issue of #E via gh issue edit --add-parent

  # --- /write-spec: parent-link resolution ---

  Scenario: Child /write-spec amends the parent spec when link resolves
    Given a committed spec at specs/feature-X/ whose Issues frontmatter is "#E"
    And a child issue whose body contains "Depends on: #E"
    When /write-spec runs on the child issue
    Then the child's content is appended to specs/feature-X/ as an amendment
    And the parent spec's Issues frontmatter is updated to include the child's number
    And a Change History row is added

  Scenario: Parent spec missing on branch fails loudly
    Given a child issue whose "Depends on: #E" resolves to an uncommitted parent spec
    When /write-spec runs on the child
    Then the skill aborts with message "Parent spec for #E not found — run '/write-spec #E' and seal the spec before starting child work"
    And no spec files are created for the child

  Scenario: No parent link falls through to keyword discovery
    Given a child issue with no "Depends on:" lines and no GitHub sub-issue parent
    When /write-spec runs
    Then parent-link resolution returns no candidates
    And the existing keyword-based spec discovery runs unchanged

  Scenario: Cyclic parent-link graph is detected
    Given issue #A body contains "Depends on: #B"
    And issue #B body contains "Depends on: #A"
    When /write-spec runs on #A
    Then parent resolution terminates with a cycle-detected error naming both #A and #B
    And no spec files are created or amended

  # --- /write-spec: seal-spec flow ---

  Scenario: Seal-spec commits the umbrella spec without version bump
    Given /write-spec produces a design.md containing a "## Multi-PR Rollout" section
    And the user approves the Phase 3 tasks summary
    When the user selects "Seal and transition"
    Then a commit is created with message "docs: seal umbrella spec for #{N}"
    And the commit stages only files under specs/{feature-name}/
    And no changes are made to plugin.json, marketplace.json, CHANGELOG.md, or VERSION
    And the branch is pushed to origin

  Scenario: Re-running seal-spec is a no-op
    Given a seal commit "docs: seal umbrella spec for #149" already exists on HEAD
    When seal-spec runs again
    Then the skill prints "Spec already sealed at commit {sha}"
    And no new commit is created

  Scenario: Seal-spec auto-executes in unattended mode when trigger fires
    Given .claude/unattended-mode exists
    And design.md contains a Multi-PR Rollout trigger
    When /write-spec approves Phase 3
    Then the seal commit and push happen without invoking AskUserQuestion
    And the child-issue batch creation runs without prompting

  # --- /open-pr: sibling-aware bumping ---

  Scenario: Intermediate child PR gets a patch bump with partial-delivery note
    Given current PR is for child issue #C of epic #E
    And at least one sibling of #C is open or has no merged PR
    When /open-pr runs
    Then the version bump is patch
    And the CHANGELOG primary bullet ends with "(partial delivery — see epic #E)"
    And the PR body footer contains "**Bump:** patch (epic child: intermediate)"

  Scenario: Final child PR gets a minor bump
    Given current PR is for child issue #C of epic #E
    And every sibling of #C is closed with a merged PR
    When /open-pr runs
    Then the version bump is minor
    And the CHANGELOG primary bullet contains no partial-delivery note
    And the PR body footer contains "**Bump:** minor (epic child: final)"

  Scenario: Non-epic PR flows through unchanged
    Given current PR is for an issue with no parent and no epic label on any referenced issue
    When /open-pr runs
    Then version bump classification matches the existing label-based rules
    And no epic classification line is added to the PR body

  Scenario: Race on plugin.json triggers rebase and re-bump without force-push
    Given /open-pr has just committed a bump to plugin.json and marketplace.json
    And origin/main has advanced (a sibling PR merged first)
    When /open-pr attempts to push
    Then git fetch detects the stale base
    And the skill rebases, re-computes the bump against the now-current plugin.json version, re-commits, and re-pushes
    And no force-push is used

  Scenario: Conflict in version files during rebase escalates without force-push
    Given rebase produces a conflict in plugin.json or marketplace.json
    When /open-pr detects the conflict
    Then the skill aborts with a conflict message naming the conflicting file
    And does not force-push under any circumstance

  Scenario: Epic closed prematurely warns the user
    Given epic issue #E has state CLOSED
    And current child issue #C has state OPEN
    When /open-pr runs for #C
    Then the skill warns "Epic #E is closed but child #C is still open — confirm the epic was not closed prematurely"
    And in interactive mode prompts for confirmation
    And in unattended mode escalates and exits without creating the PR

  # --- sdlc-runner: topological ordering ---

  Scenario: Runner skips children blocked by unmerged dependencies
    Given the milestone contains open issues #A and #B
    And #B body contains "Depends on: #A"
    And #A has no merged PR yet
    When the runner selects the next issue to process
    Then #B is skipped
    And a log line is emitted: "[runner] skipping #B — blocked by unmerged dependencies: #A"
    And #A is selected instead

  Scenario: Runner exits when every open issue is blocked
    Given every open issue in the milestone has at least one unmerged dependency
    When the runner calls selectNextIssueFromMilestone
    Then the function returns issue null
    And the runner exits with a non-zero code
    And stderr contains a diagnostic listing every blocked issue and its unresolved blockers

  Scenario: Runner re-derives the dependency graph on each tick
    Given the runner previously determined that #B was blocked
    And a human subsequently merged #B's dependency #A on GitHub
    When the runner starts a new tick
    Then the dependency graph is rebuilt from live gh issue view output
    And #B is now classified as ready
    And #B is selected

  Scenario: External dependencies are treated as satisfied
    Given #C body contains "Depends on: #X"
    And #X is not in the current milestone queue
    When the runner evaluates #C's readiness
    Then #X is treated as an external dependency and assumed satisfied
    And #C is eligible for selection subject to its in-milestone dependencies

  # --- Unattended-mode determinism for all new gates ---

  Scenario: No new AskUserQuestion call fires without an unattended-mode check
    Given .claude/unattended-mode exists
    When /draft-issue, /write-spec, or /open-pr reach any new gate added by this feature
    Then each gate's documented deterministic default fires
    And AskUserQuestion is not invoked at any new site
